{"TopicId":147823,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"Suggestion: Make wheels act like wheels instead of round sleds.","CreatedByName":"Talavar","CreatedById":75264,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-16T03:31:47Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Talavar","CreatedById":75264,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-16T03:31:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRedownloaded KSP after months of waiting for real wheel fixes.. made aircraft... skated around \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E for 2 minutes. Played with wheel traction.. skated more..\u00A0 Uninstalled... it\u0027s Still crap. We don\u0027t need wheels that slide sideways. You may now all get mad at me for being irritated. Enjoy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hary R","CreatedById":111339,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-16T05:05:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDo still play 1.1.3 or are you trying the 1.2\u00A0pre-release? Cause if wheels are still crap in 1.2 you have all the right to be frustrated.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-16T05:05:57Z\u0022 title=\u002209/16/2016 05:05  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 16, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Hary R\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Etypo\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Sharpy","CreatedById":145504,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-16T07:19:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, AIFAIK the wheels are still sleds, not real wheels. Made a rover that fills fully within frame of 4 ruggedized wheels, so no matter which way you flip it, wheels are the only thing that touches the ground. It should still drive normally if it does a wheelie and flips over - wheels still rotate in the same direction, turning left still has the inner sides of left wheels turn towards the body - I call it ambiupperous.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope, the upper face of the wheels is purely decorative, Only their bottoms provide propulsion.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDidn\u0027t work in 1.0.3, didn\u0027t work in 1.1.3, will it work in 1.2?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve_v","CreatedById":69272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-16T08:11:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222759342\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147823\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474010380\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022145504\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Sharpy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n51 minutes ago, Sharpy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwill it work in 1.2?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf the prerelease is anything to go by... nope. They\u0027re still \u003Cem\u003Enot-wheels.\u003C/em\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Speeding Mullet","CreatedById":62635,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-16T08:37:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222759178\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147823\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221473996707\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002275264\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Talavar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Talavar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe don\u0027t need wheels that slide sideways.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIRL wheels slide sideways under certain conditions. \u00A0I\u0027m sure there are people that would speak out on both sides of this argument, so\u00A0\u0022We\u0022 you do not speak for. \u00A0This has got the potential to be a popcorn thread so let me walk the line\u00A0and dig out an interesting post from May 2015 by \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/90837-murph/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002290837\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/90837-murph/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Murph\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0which may shed some light on why wheels are sleds and not wheels:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/107603-make-the-rugged-rover-wheels-work-upside-down/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=1891148\u0026amp;embedComment=1891148\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSM\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"steve_v","CreatedById":69272,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-16T08:45:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222759389\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147823\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474015039\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262635\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Speeding Mullet\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, Speeding Mullet said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhy wheels are sleds and not wheels\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLike I said, they\u0027re not-wheels. They have always been not-wheels and all the ongoing wheel related drama, since day-one, is due to this over-simplified single-point wheel simulation.\u003Cbr\u003E\nWheel is not a wheel -\u0026gt; re-invent wheel.\u003Cbr\u003E\nPhysics sim is not realistic enough -\u0026gt; fix physics sim.\u003Cbr\u003E\nReliance on unity builtins / third-party plugins limits functionality -\u0026gt; write better unity plugin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-16T08:46:10Z\u0022 title=\u002209/16/2016 08:46  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 16, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by steve_v\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003Etypos\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Curveball Anders","CreatedById":107529,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-16T08:57:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00222759393\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022147823\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221474015516\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002269272\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022steve_v\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, steve_v said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nongoing wheel related drama.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe for some ongoing wheel related drama.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP isn\u0027t a simulator, it\u0027s a game where you build stuff using it\u0027s very simplistic version of physics.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222016-09-16T08:58:17Z\u0022 title=\u002209/16/2016 08:58  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003ESeptember 16, 2016\u003C/time\u003E by Curveball Anders\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"sal_vager","CreatedById":16426,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-09-16T08:59:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCough.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/147822-suggestion-make-wheels-act-like-wheels-instead-of-round-sleds/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0026amp;comment=2759169\u0026amp;embedComment=2759169\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment#comment-2759169\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}